# Frontend Production Standards

## Folder Structure (enforced)

```
expense-tracking-frontend/src/
  config/                 # api.js, googleOAuth.js -- app-level configuration
  components/
    common/               # Cross-feature reusable components (NotificationsPanel, UniversalSearch)
    ui/                   # Primitive UI wrappers (Button, Dialog, Modal, Select, Table)
    layout/               # App shell, sidebars, navigation bars
  features/
    {feature}/
      components/         # Feature-scoped components
      pages/              # Route-level pages (one per route)
      hooks/              # Feature-scoped custom hooks
      services/           # Feature-scoped API calls (if not in Redux actions)
  pages/                  # Legacy top-level pages (AuthPage, Dashboard) -- do not add new ones here
  Redux/
    {Feature}/
      {feature}.actionType.js   # Action type constants
      {feature}.action.js       # Thunk action creators
      {feature}.reducer.js      # Reducer with switch/case
    store.js              # combineReducers + createStore + thunk middleware
  hooks/                  # Shared custom hooks (useTheme, useTranslation, useUserSettings)
  services/               # Shared API services (itemService, etc.)
  i18n/translations/      # en.js, hi.js, te.js
  shared/                 # Theme, EmojiPicker
  utils/                  # Pure utility functions (formatters, validators, fuzzyMatch)
```

Rules:
- New features go in `features/{name}/` -- never add new top-level pages to `pages/`
- Shared components go in `components/common/` or `components/ui/`
- One component per file, one page per route
- Never create a file without knowing which folder it belongs to

## Component Standards

- Functional components only; no class components (except ErrorBoundary)
- One exported component per file (Single Responsibility)
- Keep components under 80 lines; extract sub-components at that threshold
- PascalCase filenames for components (`ExpenseCard.jsx`)
- camelCase filenames for hooks, utils, services (`useExpenses.js`, `formatCurrency.js`)
- Props destructured in function parameters with defaults where sensible

## Design Patterns

### Container/Presenter

Separate data-fetching from rendering:

```
FeaturePage.jsx          # Container: useDispatch, useSelector, useEffect for data
  └── FeatureList.jsx    # Presenter: receives props, renders UI, no Redux
        └── FeatureRow   # Presenter: single item rendering
```

### Custom Hook Extraction

Extract reusable logic into hooks when:
- The same `useEffect` + `useState` pattern appears in 2+ components
- A component has more than 3 hooks -- group related ones into a custom hook
- Side effects (API calls, subscriptions, timers) can be isolated

### Render Props / Composition

Prefer composition over prop drilling:
- Wrap children in provider components for cross-cutting concerns
- Use `React.lazy` + `Suspense` at route boundaries for code splitting

## DRY Principles

- Extract shared UI patterns into `components/ui/` (buttons, dialogs, tables)
- Extract shared business logic into `hooks/` (auth checks, permission guards, formatting)
- Extract shared API call patterns into `services/` or Redux actions -- never duplicate Axios calls
- Extract shared Yup validation schemas into `utils/validation.js` when used by 2+ forms
- Translation keys: reuse `common.*` keys for shared text; feature-specific keys for unique text

### DRY Violations to Watch For

| Smell | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Same API call in multiple components | Extract to Redux action or shared service |
| Same form validation in multiple forms | Extract to `utils/validation.js` |
| Same loading/error UI in multiple pages | Extract to `components/common/AsyncWrapper.jsx` |
| Same date/currency formatting in multiple places | Extract to `utils/formatters.js` |
| Same auth guard logic in multiple routes | Extract to `components/common/ProtectedRoute.jsx` |

## State Management Rules

- Redux + Thunk for server state and global app state (auth, expenses, budgets)
- `useState` for local component UI state only (modals open/close, form dirty state)
- Never put derived data in Redux -- compute it with `useMemo` in the component
- Never mutate Redux state directly; always return new objects in reducers
- Action types follow the pattern: `{VERB}_{NOUN}_{STATUS}` (e.g., `CREATE_EXPENSE_SUCCESS`)

## Environment Configuration

- All environment variables prefixed with `REACT_APP_`
- Define in `.env.local` (dev), `.env.production` (prod) -- never commit `.env.local`
- Access via `process.env.REACT_APP_*` -- never hard-code URLs or secrets
- Provide fallback defaults in `config/api.js`: `process.env.REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL || "http://localhost:8080"`
- Document every env var in `.env.example` with placeholder values

## Build Readiness Checklist

Before any feature is considered complete:

- [ ] No `console.log`, `debugger`, or `alert()` statements
- [ ] No unused imports or variables (will fail lint)
- [ ] No hard-coded strings -- all user-facing text uses `t()`
- [ ] No hard-coded colors -- all use MUI theme tokens
- [ ] No hard-coded URLs -- all use `config/api.js` constants
- [ ] Loading state shown for all async operations
- [ ] Error state shown with retry option for all async operations
- [ ] New translation keys added to all 3 files (en, hi, te)
- [ ] Component under 80 lines
- [ ] No prop drilling deeper than 2 levels -- use Redux or context
- [ ] `useEffect` has proper cleanup and correct dependency array
- [ ] Route is lazy-loaded with `React.lazy` + `Suspense`
- [ ] No secrets or API keys in committed code
- [ ] JWT stored in memory or httpOnly cookie, not `localStorage` (migration in progress)
- [ ] `npm run build` completes without errors or warnings

## Import Order

```jsx
// 1. React and core libraries
import React, { useState, useEffect, useMemo, useCallback } from "react";
import { useDispatch, useSelector } from "react-redux";
import { useNavigate, useParams } from "react-router-dom";

// 2. MUI components
import { Box, Typography, Button, CircularProgress, Alert } from "@mui/material";
import AddIcon from "@mui/icons-material/Add";

// 3. Project components
import PageHeader from "../../../components/PageHeader";
import DataCard from "../../../components/common/DataCard";

// 4. Hooks
import { useTheme } from "../../../hooks/useTheme";
import { useTranslation } from "../../../hooks/useTranslation";

// 5. Redux actions
import { fetchExpensesAction } from "../../../Redux/Expenses/expense.action";

// 6. Utils and services
import { formatCurrency } from "../../../utils/formatters";
```

## Performance Rules

- `useMemo` for expensive computations (sorting, filtering large arrays)
- `useCallback` for handlers passed to memoized children
- `React.memo` on pure presentational components receiving object/array props
- Virtualize lists with 100+ items (`react-window` or `react-virtualized`)
- Lazy-load routes; never import all pages eagerly
- Import MUI components individually, not from barrel exports
